The High Court Sitting In Kisumu Has Granted The Prosecution 11 Days To Conclude Investigations Into The Murder Of Journalist Eric Oloo. The Number Of Suspects Has Also Now Reduced To Two. These Are Brothers Victor Ogola Lutta And Joel Lutta.The Case Will Next Be Mentioned On 10th December. A Preliminary Postmortem Report Indicated That Oloo Died As A Result Of Excessive Bleeding. The Report Said The Body Had A Blunt Injury On The Head And That There Was Severe Bleeding In The Stomach. Oloo's Body Was Found In The House Of The Unguja Deputy OCS Sabina Kerubo.